He stresses the importance of first excluding the presence of bats before maintenance work in the goods, as it is possible that the involuntary destruction of a single nesting site could kill up to 400 females and young animals and wipe out the entire population on site.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill them, harass them, or destroy their nest sites.
Elizabeth Ferrell, Scottish official of the Bat Conservation Trust, encouraged the population to help.
